<br>
You’re right, a lot of people do use this as an escape. I know I did. /shrug<br>
When it was time to return to RL, I went back to RL. If anything, I enjoy the game more now, since it’s not <I>survival</I> anymore... it’s a game, a pasttime...<br>
<br>
Addictive games attract addictive people and in turn encourage addictive behavior. I have a hard time believing that anyone can get “sucked in” and have their lives turned upside-down by EQ. The problem was extant, then magnified when the escape of EQ presented itself. People with addictive personalities have trouble escaping EQ’s grasp, sometimes “quitting” four, five, or six times and still never completely letting go. They need the fiction that they are important, needed, and/or special. But really, if you tell random_joe_02 walking by that you play a 60 monk with an epic and full NtoV armor, does anyone care?<br>
<br>
It’s a game. It’s a game with a strong community feel to it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<I>I've made the decision myself to completely quit. No more going back for me as I will probably delete my characters and tear up the CD's. Once that is done, I will never go back and I'll probably be the better for it.</I><br>
<br>
If that is your decision, then I’m sure we’ll all wish you well. Your community and your friends will miss you.<br>
